From Kevin Weinrich Subject SUMMARY How to make a window's input be ALL CAPS Thanks to Bruce Barnett who recommended xvttool and Bernward Averwald and Liam Quin who recommended modifying to get the desired behavior for a class of In xvttool simply create a key file that looks like a A b B c C and specify said key file on the command This will translate any input into any other in my case lo case to up case Works great and you get a customizable button pad on the right or left To use an xterm solution add to your capxterm override Key a string A n or override n Key a insert string A n Key b insert string B n and invoke as xterm name capxterm Thanks loads Kevin Weinrich Computer Sciences